  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Coverage promise",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "# GitHub Copilot OTel coverage, local reality check\n\nThis dashboard answers: **which signals from the monitoring article have actually appeared in your local telemetry?**\n\n- **Observed** means the signal appeared in Prometheus or Tempo.\n- **Not observed yet** means the stack is ready, but you have not triggered that behavior locally, or the current emitter did not send that field.\n- This dashboard does not use synthetic usage data. The only synthetic part is the audit metadata row that says whether a signal was observed.\n- Content capture is verified by attribute presence and size, not by showing raw prompt or code in Grafana.\n- Official usage/billing still comes from GitHub APIs and billing exports."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Metrics observed",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 7
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus-local"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum(max_over_time(copilot_otel_coverage_status_ratio{signal_type=~\".*metric.*\", status=\"observed\"}[$__range])) or vector(0)",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "prometheus-local"
          }
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "graphMode": "none",
        "colorMode": "value"
      }
    },
    {
