              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "options": {
        "showHeader": true,
        "cellHeight": "sm"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "How to make missing signals appear",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 9,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 33
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Missing does not mean broken\n\nSome fields appear only when that behavior happens. Current typical gaps are expected unless you trigger them:\n\n- **User actions and feedback:** copy/insert/apply/follow-up actions and thumbs up/down.\n- **Cloud and PR flows:** cloud session start, PR creation, PR-ready notification.\n- **MCP-specific tool calls:** MCP server name, MCP server hash, MCP tool name.\n- **Cache creation tokens:** appears only when the runtime reports cache creation, not every request.\n- **Hooks:** configure and trigger hooks to see `execute_hook` and hook attributes.\n- **Repository tags:** open a Git repo, register the workspace, and reload VS Code before starting the session.\n\nThis dashboard is a coverage checklist for local validation, not a generated usage report."
      }
    }
  ],
